contentrichtext.text: '''Wichita''' is the name of: *[[Wichita people]], a Native American tribe *[[Wichita language]], the language of the tribe '''Wichita''' may also refer to: {{TOCright}} ==Places== ;United States *[[Wichita, Kansas]] *[[Wichita County, Kansas]] *[[Wichita County, Texas]] *[[Wichita Falls, Texas]] *[[Lake Wichita|Wichita Lake]], Texas *[[Wichita Mountains]], a small mountain range in southwest Oklahoma *[[Wichita River]], a tributary of the Red River in Texas *[[Wichita State University]], located in the city of Wichita, Kansas ==In the military== *{{sclass-|Wichita|cruiser|2}}, a heavy cruiser class of the US Navy **{{USS|Wichita|CA-45}}, the only ship of the class; active in World War II *{{sclass-|Wichita|replenishment oiler|2}}, a class of US Navy oilers from the late 1960s to the mid-1990s **{{USS|Wichita|AOR-1}}, the lead ship of the class; in service from 1969 to 1993 *[[Beechcraft AT-10 Wichita]], a World War II trainer airplane for the United States Army Air Forces ==In entertainment== *[[Wichita (1955 film)|''Wichita'' (1955 film)]], an American Western movie directed by Jacques Tourneur *[[Wichita (2010 film)|''Wichita'' (2010 film)]], a film starring Cameron Diaz and Tom Cruise *[[Wichita Recordings]], a London based independent record label ==See also== *[[Ouachita (disambiguation)]] *[[Washita (disambiguation)]] {{disambig}}
